    <stitle>CE 200, CE 300 - HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - REMOVE - External Block Heater Connection</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>External Block Heater Connection</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Block Heater Connection - Remove / Install</title>
            <para>The optional block heater receptacle is located in the lower center portion of the bumper opening. It
                is mounted on a bracket and bolted to the lower bumper opening flange.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To remove the receptacle, unplug the connection at the rear of the heater receptacle.
                    Push in on plug connection to release lock and pull plug out to remove.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate and remove the lower mounting bolts on the bumper flange.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the receptacle.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Follow the reverse procedure to install.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f09009110" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G09009110.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
